				<table width="100%" cellspacing="5">
				<tr>
					<td>
					

						<div class="postbody">In addition to using OR to set bits and AND to clear them, you can use XOR (exclusive OR) to invert them. When you XOR a bit with 0, it remains unaltered, but if you XOR it with 1, it gets inverted (1 becomes 0 and 0 becomes 1). In 6502 assembly, the command that performs a XOR is called EOR. I don't know if this will be useful to you in this particular project, but I though I'd just mention another type of manipulation you can do to bits.</div>

					<br clear="all" /><br />

						<table width="100%" cellspacing="0">
